The feeding of an obese child: don't eat breakfast and take charcuterie for dinner
Over one third of children aged 9 to 13 have overweight problems, 9% of schoolchildren will be overweight and 5% will be obese.
As current research shows, obese children come from families with a unhealthy lifestyle.
This shows again how important is the environment in which the human being evolves and the models surrounding him.
For example, 50% more often than in normal-weighted children's families are found on obese children's tables.
19% of the obese had fries at dinner according to the investigation carried out with an awareness action " Obesity is not a coincidence"
In the families of small adults sport is also not a habit, which is now the case of most schoolchildren today - only 15% answered that at least once a week the parents found time for active movement.
Survey of 900 children
The survey took place during the last school year and participated in 900 primary schools in Czech Republic.
It was the second edition of " Obesity is not a coincidence", action supported by the General Health Insurance and Unilever society.
Since the beginning, more than 12000 sixth to third students have enrolled in this project.
One of the determining factors that cause a dramatic increase in the number of overweight, or even obese children, is the absence, correct diet and not enough physical exercise.
"Only half of the children questioned indicate, for example, eating 5 times a day breakfast in case - lunch - taste- dinner, which is a basic principle of good food," indicates one of the results of the survey.
No breakfast and charcuterie at dinner
Specialists draw attention to the fact that to have healthy development we need some basic details such as a family breakfast at the same time.
In Czech, only 23% of the pupils' families eat at the same time.
In most families everyone has breakfast alone.
And the worst thing that's been noticed is that a tenth of the population doesn't have breakfast at all.
Breakfast is, however, the basis of a good daily diet.
The questionnaire showed that obese children's families consume unhealthy fries more often.
Almost every student - not to mention weight - drinks daily (70%).
More than 40% of the children questioned do sports regularly but for parents it is half, only 15%.
Prepare your food
Another part of the survey allowed selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to prepare their own food based on opportunities offered according to their own taste and personal opinion.
"The preferences of Czech children between 12 and 15 years of age are far from ideal for healthy eating."
Among their favorite dishes are many cakes, meats and sugars.
"The most alarming is, in particular, a great preference for sweet lemonades," is indicated in the results of the investigation.
For lunch are the pasta that took first place right in front of the white meat.
Children did not want to be fertile at all, and the preference for fish and vegetable meals was very low.
Head of Health
The survey also showed that children are ready to change their habits from the time they receive ad hoc information.
"In the course of a review of a group of survey participants who had completed the questionnaire after the awareness session " Obesity is not a coincidence," we saw a strong desire to move towards healthy food," the results of the survey indicate.
For example, the most striking was for sweet lemonades because children began to give preference to drinking water.
Children most often checked the questionnaire for white meat and fish as main dish and would reduce sweet dishes and "knedliky" (Czech speciality of bread flour or potatoes).
