The need for speed The Run fights across America.
By Way of Review
Originally, a race without problems is transformed by a set of stupid mistakes of people who have nothing to do with a routine morning shift at work.
This fills up to a certain extent the ambition of each but it is of no use if no one wants to do anything more.
The new part entitled The Run produced great expectations before its release.
He promised to take a new direction with the already old Need for Speed race series and to get out of some sort of game from the playable parts that would not just count on points.
So we were curious how the passages added during which the main hero came out of his car and did what he wanted.
As already in the NFS series, the result is completely different from what was expected.
They are potentially arcade racing games but the whole pulls down because of some unnecessary mistakes that have already existed for several years.
These are not really errors but rather the expression of an incomprehensible fannery on the part of the developers.
The adventure begins very well.
You are caught up in the adventure of which the main hero Jack has character problems and in order to solve them he gets to participate in illegal races across America.
You are sitting behind the wheel on the west coast of San Francisco and your mission is to arrive first in New York.
The idea has interesting elements.
The route is divided into ten stages and then into more than 50 races.
The result is that each race takes place on another route and the stages envisaged in different environments that distinguish each other quite well and are interesting.
The player does not have the feeling that the game offers him something identical.
Some environments are rather beautiful even though the graphic technical level is the same as the previous series.
It's not the end of the world.
But driving through the desert, in autumn landscapes or in highly snowy mountains is very pleasant visually.
The tests are more time-consuming with an atypical element.
For example in the desert you find yourself in a sandstorm that significantly reduces your visibility.
Then in the mountains you must be careful that an avalanche does not fall upon you.
Next to this the different races are well arranged behind each other.
There are only a small number of them, but that's enough.
There are moments you try to exceed the requested number of opponents (like in a classic race) then run against the watch (classic duel with the timer) and then wait for another duel with an opponent.
From time to time you also have the police that enter the game and try to make your situation difficult.
The novelty is the out-of-vehicle passages.
It's rather an interactive animation when most of the time Jack runs away from someone and you need to help him by taping the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
What is surprising is that there are fewer times like this than you expect (to be concrete there are only three).
The result is as well because this element is not likely to interfere and places itself, in the context described above, in the elements that enhance the game.
The driving model is in the tradition of previous games.
Which means that at present there is nothing extraordinary but it cannot be said to be negative.
With regard to realistic simulation you will have to go and see elsewhere.
But although we can better find in the competition the driving model goes very well with the type of race design.
So everything's okay.
Problems begin to appear after some time.
Unlike the driving model, collisions have not yet been completed.
We do not expect a complicated deformation and collisions from this game, but when you do not have, during a collision with any object, the slightest idea of how your car behaves, it is therefore not completely good.
During tight overruns you sometimes touch each other slightly but otherwise your car goes into crazy rusts.
Or it's in socks.
Thanks to the restart system this is not really a problem but it really bothers you.
The restart is done in such a way that when you have broken your face or you have gone out into the game decor brings you back at the time of the last point on the itinerary.
But you only have 5 restarts.
When you have used the 5 restarts you have to restart the game from the beginning.
So it's more a tool, in case something doesn't happen as it should, than something you can really count on.
Sometimes restarts do not help and you need to find the solution by remembering the part of the route in question.
The big hic of this game is that the same actions are found in the same places.
For example, there are some turns that need to be done in a certain way, otherwise it does not happen.
Otherwise you meet in a given place "civil vehicles" always in the same configuration as you arrived first, fifth, 5 seconds in advance or a minute late.
What makes you angry are the situations when you easily pass the opponent between two cars coming backwards and when you get there, you need either to stand aside and turn around or to slow them down.
It's equal if you go ahead of him because it's "calculated" so that for the given situation it always happens close to your nose.
Opponents still have other advantages.
All the time of the game, you arrive in some places, again without worrying about the time, and you still have the same opponent that precedes you in the same place.
This gets the most annoying at the end of the game when you ride on a long bridge in the opposite direction.
The opponent must at any cost pass before you.
When it passes before you it hides the sight of other vehicles in reverse and you collide a lot of times.
You can understand that the purpose of this game is to do something captivating and full of adrenaline, but it is clear that you are bored quickly.
And it's bad because through a simple driving model the game is interesting and places with so much action that you don't have time to follow everything that happens.
And it's equal if it's because of the concept of 50 unique routes, that the order of the races is such that there's no chance of getting bored or anything else.
The original idea is the car change during the races.
You need to be careful about petrol pumps on the routes because you can change cars however most of the time the one you have enough.
Cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are ideal for cities, large U.S. bicycles for straight highways and super sports cars at exotic sights on very technical pipelines, for example on lace roads in the mountains.
And the way of challenges, which are races in particular places you know about adventure, goes very well with the main regime of history.
You receive not only medals but also points of experience that add to your profile that are common to challenges and adventure.
When you have reached the highest level of driver, different objects begin to unwind:
This one connects online with the Autolog function that compares your results with those of other players and provides you with other functions in the community.
One of the most difficult shots to understand is the situation of the last race of adventure.
You arrive with your car in the subway tunnel (like this) where you ride in the darkness on the tracks (like this).
Your speed indicator tells you between 150 and 200 km/h (a priori) and behind you comes a subway branch that sends the car directly to the hardware.
At the writing we had a discussion for a few days whether someone really thought about the creation of this game or whether the authors really think of us as idiots.
The technical part of the game is not extra, but the visual part is generally pleasant and in some cases really great.
What's bothering is that in more extreme situations, imaging does not hold the level and in some cases tragically.
This mainly concerns accidents with a large number of participants when a fluid imaging is no longer useful to you.
The sound part is good and the track is in choice.
In order to please the greatest number and especially the young public a new soundtrack has been created in the "I mix everything" style, but one can expect that no one will buy the game for music.
General impression of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore really confused.
If the game did not have these stupid mistakes we could say without fear that it is the best production of NFS in recent years.
But this game gives the impression that it's not over.
The fun is really good but prepare yourself to have the faults hit your eyes with the strength of an aerodrome reflector.
The Velvet Students in concert with the choirs of Charles University
The Festival Fiesta Academica offers for the third time festivals that connect the International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velor Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival there are 20 choirs of high schools and secondary classes.
The festival was set up in two concerts organized on 17 November.
"Charles University has an important part in this festival."
"Of the choirs there is the Choeur of the Faculty of Pedagogy and Humanities, on the festival committee sits the rector Vaclav Hampl," says the leader of the organizing team Jakub Calou.
The highlight of the festival is the Choeur des lycées and secondary classes concert that takes place with free entrance on November 17 from 14 hours on the space located in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
In the program there is the composition of the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz mass.
In the evening the concert "Speed Students" takes place in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady during which the choirs of the higher schools as well as that of Charles University are produced.
The aim of the Festival Academica is not only to celebrate the International Day of Students with dignity and recall the 22nd anniversary of the velour revolution, but also to present to the public a choir music of the highest level and to develop creative cooperation of young people.
The main organizer is the Union of Czech Fathers in cooperation with the Jan Kepler High School.
All the action is placed under the aegis of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, Rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
The program also offers high-level concerts, Mexican meetings, student chatting and other activities.
The interested parties will find all the information on the Internet pages of the festival www.festaacademica.cz.
