History of a brand:
IBM innovator begins the second century of its existence
If anyone were to look for the word that expresses the IBM strategy as closely as possible, the closest one would be "the long term".
For a wide audience IBM is the symbol of the technological revolution, it is a firm felt as very current and yet since its creation it has been 100 years.
The basis of this long-term strategy was laid by the first head of the firm, visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He left this slogan that a large number of global problems can be solved for little if people are willing to think.
His slogan "PENSE" has become the footprint around which the life of a future giant will develop (and also the title of the internal magazine IBM began to edit in 1935).
It was the basis of the culture of the carefully developed company by Watson.
For us IBM means a long-term thought of continuous forward-looking movements.
IBM survived a hundred years due to the fact that it remained faithful to its basic values and yet was not afraid to change all the others around it.
This allowed us in the first century to transform technology, business and society.
We hope that in the second century we will achieve even more" has released for the anniversary the current director of Samuel J. Palmisano.
A well-prepared system
Watson, in the 1930s, took care of his employees as Bata in the Czech Republic - IBM people were the only ones among the first U.S. employees to have paid vacations, an insurance paid by the employer plus an elegant employee uniform and a well-designed system of rewards for inventors and traders.
Similarly IBM has a well-developed customer relationship system.
The society was at the very beginning in the discovery of talents—as one of the first firms to have abolished any form of discrimination and thus could have the choice.
The current plan is entirely in the spirit of the anti-discrimination strategy as it will be a woman- Virginia Rometty - who should replace Palmisano with the head of IBM.
She has been working with IBM for 30 years and is currently serving as Chief of Sales, Marketing and Strategy.
IBM over the past few years has done what is known as jamy, brainstorming online, from which many future strategies and innovations have emerged.
It is not surprising that there are many ideas - in the firm there are nearly 500,000 people who work.
An institution with a good name
It is the internal and external image of the company that gives it a secure position in the business field.
"Since the beginning IBM had a concept rather than a technological firm," said Rosabeth Moss Kanter, Economic Professor at Harvard Economics School and author of the book on IBM.
