The famous Scott Peterson took off using the past while claiming that his murdered wife was alive, triggering a national search to find her.
Deceptional individuals can also use a remote language: "I have not had sexual relations with this woman... Miss Lewinsky" or repeat completely a difficult question.
The most common verbal indicators are subtle.
Someone can use a lot of "wood tongue" in his answer to a difficult question: "Well... to say the truth... if I remember well... to my knowledge."
This makes the response perceptual rather than factual and is often a red flag.
There is no magic formula for the detection of lies, but the development of skills to recognize deception is possible.
