This is an excerpt from the conversation, whose complete transcription is found in La Nación on the Internet.
For his Costa Rican followers, the fact that Pearl Jam will happen in Costa Rica is a dream come true. Are you aware of what your fans are living?
Going to Costa Rica is a dream that has become a reality for us too.
This is our second time in South and Central America and so far it has been great.
I spent only once on vacation in Costa Rica; it's such a beautiful country and I think we can spend a few days there.
We are therefore moved to bring our music there.
I ask you, because there is some kind of devotion to the group, fans live with intensity the previous days.
What is your message for your most fervent followers?
Thank you for staying with us all these years.
It took 21 years for us to arrive in Costa Rica; thank you for waiting so long and we are sorry that it has been so long since this concert.
Some people already say his concert is the biggest show of the year.
Does this add some pressure to your visit.
Some of the biggest shows we've had in the last 21 years have been held in the last two weeks.
