Thus was the work of the person of Cali who identified the corpse of Alfonso Cano
A California dactyloscope went to history like the man who confirmed the death of "Alfonso Cano".
The work of these staff members is crucial.
On November 4th, a typist from the CTI of Cali went to history as the person who confirmed the identity of the Supreme Chief of the Farcs: "Alfonso Cano", confronting his fingerprints.
Of the seven dactyloscopes working in the local offices of the ITC, this week was the "availability" tour of Eliazar González, a man from Puerto Tejada who has worked in the field of judicial investigation for 21 years.
At the beginning of his career, González worked in the municipalities of Chocó, where he often spent more than five days in the forest to reach the place where the bodies were to be identified.
The year 2000 he moved to the capital of Valle and after taking adequate courses, he specialized in typyloscopy, which is the study of friction skin, i.e. palms and feet.
During the week of the operation against alias Alfonso Cano, Eliasar was advised to take clothes with him for at least three days.
Something very big was waiting for him.
Friday night he left for Cauca in a Palmira helicopter.
He knew he had to identify two corpses and one of them was suspected to be the man who was leading the oldest guerrilla in the world, so he was asked to take the map with the ten fingerprints of Guillermo León Sáenz (his real name).
But when he arrived with the investigation team at the site of the body, he did not recognize him by his physical appearance, because he was very different from the one he had seen in the media.
He had no beard, he was dressed like a peasant in the area, without glasses and much thinner.
But the prints don't lie.
Accompanied by a Galtonian magnifying glass, ink, picker and lantern, Eliazar compared the fingerprints of the corpse with those of the card.
His eye did not deceive him: it was "Alfonso Cano".
That same night, the man from Puerto Tejada was responsible for confirming to the Minister of Defense, Juan Carlos Pinzón that yes, he was the Supreme Chief of the Farcs.
In search of the fingerprint
For a Dactyloscopeist from Sijín de Cali the recognition that President Juan Manuel Santos made to Eliazar González in a press conference for the operation against "Cano", is very significant.
A lot of people don't know our work.
Dactyloscopy is an accurate science, without any margin of error, which can be crucial in resolving crimes.
Apart from identifying the bodies, the dactyloscopeists support investigations into crimes such as theft and murder and confirm the identity of the captured persons.
When captured, many offenders present false identity cards or do not have documents.
We take their fingerprints and search them in the database.
The researcher said that in a case of theft he had to remove part of the wall of a house, because in this place the thief had supported his hand to bring out a safe full of jewelry and money.
"The walls are difficult because they are not adequate surfaces to draw a fingerprint on them, but in this case we were able to get the fingerprint from all hands and identify the offender who had participated in various flights," he recalls.
The fingerprints may also exclude or confirm suspects in cases of murder.
We recently found a dead man with bottles of drink around him.
Through the investigation it was determined that a parent may be suspected of the crime and indeed a mark on the bottle coincided.
Although it does not guarantee that he is the killer, it puts him on the scene of the crime.
One ITC fingerprinter explained that "digital fingerprints of objects with chemical or physical reagents" are extracted.
When they appear, a picker or band is used to remove them.
Later, fingerprints are sent to Asif, the declining database, or to the National Civil Registry.
"The problem is that there are still many Colombians without papers," said the ITC expert.
He explained that everything is not how it is shown in the CSI television program.
Like everything that shines is not gold, everything that you touch does not necessarily become a footprint.
However, it can be used if the necessary confrontation is achieved.
