The Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD) noted that the majority of member countries presented clearer signals of economic slowdown in September.
The indicator that anticipates the inflection points of the world economy has highlighted that the main powers are hampered.
Because it dropped four decimals to 100.4 points, compared to 100.8 in August.
