However, the Moleskine booklet as we know it today was born... in 1997.
The Italian company Modo Modo, based in Milan, decided at the time to launch a design but distinguished notebook.
Maria Sebregondi, then consultant for the company, is responsible for the launch of the new product.
The paper is inspired by an old production technique, the mole skin skin skin, which refers to a varnish cotton used to cover banquets, for example.
